The article discusses the honoring of Seraph Young Ford, the first woman to cast a ballot in an American election. She cast her historic vote in 1870 in Salt Lake City, Utah, after the territory extended voting rights to women. Seraph Young Ford was the grand-niece of Brigham Young and later moved to Maryland. She was buried in Arlington National Cemetery alongside her husband, a Union Army veteran. The article also mentions the recent celebration of the 100th anniversary of the ratification of the Nineteenth Amendment, which granted women the right to vote. The Trump Administration is highlighted for its commitment to championing women's economic empowerment through initiatives such as the Women's Global Development and Prosperity Initiative and efforts to combat human trafficking. The article emphasizes the importance of women's economic empowerment in creating peaceful and prosperous societies worldwide.